    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @ivanmmurciaua \r\n\r\nPlease keep in mind that our implementation of ERC1155 follows [the standard](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155). If you think there is a fundamental issue with the standard, I don't think this is the right place to have this discussion. You should rather go to the [Ethereum magicians forum](https://ethereum-magicians.org/).\r\n\r\nYou point being about approvals, it would be part of cross-contract interactions (and should probably be natively recognized by wallets as an approval operation). This makes me thing that standardisation of the interface is important (this is why I think it needs to be discussed with the eth magicians before we implement it)",
